reviews.text: There is a worship service filled with the Holy Spirit and full of grace every week.

While traveling around the world with my family, I attended a service at the Full Gospel Church in Singapore. It was surprising and new because all of the congregants were young people. I never imagined that we would be able to hold a worship service so full of grace in Singapore.

The praise team's praise, the choir's singing, the pastor's sermon, and the delicious table fellowship after the service were all so good and perfect.

If you visit Singapore, I highly recommend attending. We sincerely thank you for your warm hospitality to our traveler family.

I really liked the pastor’s sermon.
It was a great comfort to me
I'm so glad I stopped by before heading to the airport.
Previously, we used to worship at Trinity Church across the street, but now we have a small chapel here on the 10th floor. I enjoyed the gracious worship.
While I was in Singapore, I stopped by to worship and they treated me so well that I am leaving a review. It's a church with lots of energy because there are a lot of young people.
